WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.569 --> 00:00:02.701
Stock levels are established to maintain

2
00:00:02.701 --> 00:00:06.369
constant availability of expendable items.

3
00:00:06.369 --> 00:00:10.164
It is very important to avoid overstocking and understocking

4
00:00:10.164 --> 00:00:13.645
in both the primary and secondary inventories.

5
00:00:13.645 --> 00:00:17.442
Levels for on-demand or just-in-case items must be kept

6
00:00:17.442 --> 00:00:20.471
at a minimum to avoid overstocking,

7
00:00:20.471 --> 00:00:22.443
and separate requirements are established

8
00:00:22.443 --> 00:00:25.892
for managing and monitoring these items.

9
00:00:25.892 --> 00:00:27.331
It takes a lot of work to find

10
00:00:27.331 --> 00:00:30.088
the balance to stock in storage areas.

11
00:00:30.088 --> 00:00:33.287
As a result, it is important to keep open lines

12
00:00:33.287 --> 00:00:35.671
of communication with your customer.

13
00:00:35.671 --> 00:00:38.628
If items need to be removed or there is an increase

14
00:00:38.628 --> 00:00:41.259
in usage, you customer will be the best source

15
00:00:41.259 --> 00:00:43.670
for this kind of information.

16
00:00:43.670 --> 00:00:47.837
For more information, refer to VHA directive 1761,

17
00:00:48.700 --> 00:00:51.450
parentheses one, item number two.

